            <q>Ultimately, what is the moral difference between rearing an animal to eat it or to wear it? Mr Morley says that there is one, but to the animal there is none".&#x2014;[<a href="/lords/2000/jul/19/fur-farming-prohibition-bill#column_1138"><span class="italic">Official Report,</span> 19/7/00; col. 1138.</a>]</q>
            Who said that? It was the noble Baroness, Lady Mallalieu, in her Second Reading speech.
          </p>
